{"word":"H1735 - דֹּודָוָהוּ - Dôwdâvâhûw - do-daw-vaw'-hoo - Dodavah","slug":"H1735","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">דֹּודָוָהוּ</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>Dôwdâvâhûw"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>do-daw-vaw'-hoo"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Dodavah"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"Original: <b><he>דּודוהוּ</he></b> <p />Transliteration: <b>dôdâvâhû</b> <p />Phonetic: <b>do-daw-vaw'-hoo</b> <p class=\"bdb_def\"><b>BDB Definition</b>:</p> Dodavah = \"beloved of Jehovah\" <ol><li>a man of Mareshah in Judah, the father of Eliezer, who denounced Jehoshaphat's alliance with Ahaziah</li></ol> <p />Origin: from <a href=\"#/H1730\">H1730</a> and <a href=\"#/H3050\">H3050</a> <p />TWOT entry: None <p />Part(s) of speech: Proper Name Masculine "},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H1730\">H1730</a>, <a href=\"#/H1731\">H1731</a>, <a href=\"#/H1732\">H1732</a>, <a href=\"#/H1733\">H1733</a>, <a href=\"#/H1734\">H1734</a>, <a href=\"#/H1736\">H1736</a>, <a href=\"#/H1737\">H1737</a>"}]}